 %
 ```
 
+### Noisy git wrapper must not leak into the script
+
+A git wrapper on PATH may ignore `--quiet` and write clone progress to stdout.
+That output must not end up in the generated static load script. stderr is
+discarded here so only the script (stdout) is compared.
+
+```zsh
+% function git { [[ "$1" == clone ]] && print "NOISY-GIT: clone progress on stdout"; mockgit "$@" }
+% antidote bundle fakeuser/fakerepo 2>/dev/null | subenv ANTIDOTE_HOME
+fpath+=( "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo" )
+source "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo/fakerepo.plugin.zsh"
+% function git { mockgit "$@" }
+%
+```
+
