 ```
 
+Clone stdout must not leak into the generated script.
+
+A git wrapper on PATH may ignore `--quiet` and write progress to stdout. Since
+antidote-script emits the load script on stdout, that text must be routed to
+stderr so it can't pollute the script. Diagnostics remain visible on stderr.
+
+```zsh
+% function git { [[ "$1" == clone ]] && print "NOISY-GIT: clone progress on stdout"; mockgit "$@" }
+% antidote-script --kind clone bar/foo 2>/dev/null
+% function git { mockgit "$@" }
+%
+```
